# 6. ROLLUP

## Purpose

Creates hierarchical subtotals and a Grand Total automatically.

### Example

```sql
SELECT
    CardCode,
    SlpCode,
    SUM(DocTotal)
FROM OINV
GROUP BY ROLLUP
(
    CardCode,
    SlpCode
);
```

### Output

| Customer | Salesperson | Sales |
|-----------|-------------|------:|
| C001 | John | 50,000 |
| C001 | Mike | 40,000 |
| C001 | NULL | 90,000 *(Subtotal)* |
| C002 | John | 70,000 |
| C002 | NULL | 70,000 *(Subtotal)* |
| NULL | NULL | 160,000 *(Grand Total)* |

### Best Use Cases

- Region → City
- Year → Month
- Department → Employee

---

# 7. CUBE

## Purpose

Creates every possible subtotal combination.

### Example

```sql
SELECT
    CardCode,
    SlpCode,
    SUM(DocTotal)
FROM OINV
GROUP BY CUBE
(
    CardCode,
    SlpCode
);
```

### Produces

- Customer totals
- Salesperson totals
- Customer + Salesperson totals
- Grand Total

### Best Use Cases

Cross-dimensional business analysis.

---

# 8. GROUPING SETS

## Purpose

Generates only the summaries you explicitly request.

### Example

```sql
SELECT
    CardCode,
    SlpCode,
    SUM(DocTotal)
FROM OINV
GROUP BY GROUPING SETS
(
    (CardCode),
    (SlpCode)
);
```

Produces only:

- Customer totals
- Salesperson totals

No unnecessary subtotal combinations.

---

# 9. ROLLUP vs CUBE vs GROUPING SETS

| Feature | ROLLUP | CUBE | GROUPING SETS |
|----------|--------|------|---------------|
| Hierarchical Subtotals | ✅ | ❌ | Custom |
| Grand Total | ✅ | ✅ | Optional |
| Every Combination | ❌ | ✅ | Only Selected |
| Performance | Fast | Slowest | Efficient |
| Best For | Hierarchical Reports | Multi-dimensional Analysis | Custom Reports |

